26/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- After an extraordinary session of Bulgaria's government Monday (25 October), Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov sealed an order that relocates Bulgarian troops in Iraq from Karbala to Diwania by 20 November.
The long-expected decision came after months of discussion and controversy in Sofia.
In other news, the US European Command's Chief of Staff, Lieutenant General Colby Broadwater, visited Sofia on Monday.
He pledged continued US support for defence sector reforms and military staff training.
(Monitor, Sega - 26/10/04;
Bulgarian government Web site - 25/10/04)
